
// This Hyperlambda code concatenates a SQL query string by using the [strings.concat] slot. It retrieves the current SQL string from the [.sql] node, appends " from opportunities where keyword_count > 0" to it, and then updates the [.sql] node with the new concatenated string using the [set-value] slot. The code effectively builds a SQL query to select data from the "opportunities" table where the "keyword_count" is greater than zero.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat:x:@.sql
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:" from "
      .:opportunities
      .:" where keyword_count > 0"
